                            <comment id="16595262" author="rfscholte" created="Tue, 28 Aug 2018 16:40:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This might have to do with a discussion with the openJDK team. Groovy used to look into &lt;tt&gt;META-INF/services/org.codehaus.groovy.runtime.ExtensionModule&lt;/tt&gt; but this is &lt;b&gt;&lt;em&gt;not&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/b&gt; a service as can be used by the &lt;a href=&quot;https://docs.oracle.com/javase/9/docs/api/java/util/ServiceLoader.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;ServiceLoader&lt;/a&gt;. This caused issues since Java 9, because the java compiler started to validate all these files.&lt;br/&gt;
It seems that they&apos;ve solved this by moving it to a difference directory (the only right solution IMHO). To stay backwards compatible both files should be shaded IMO.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17030973" author="rfscholte" created="Wed, 5 Feb 2020 19:54:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed in &lt;a href=&quot;https://gitbox.apache.org/repos/asf?p=maven-shade-plugin.git;a=commit;h=799e02abdf936d6f83026403a5ed64e70ad920ef&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;799e02abdf936d6f83026403a5ed64e70ad920ef&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17030990" author="hudson" created="Wed, 5 Feb 2020 20:09:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Build succeeded in Jenkins: Maven TLP &#187; maven-shade-plugin &#187; master #56&lt;/p&gt;

